PN,41611
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1772755384
OL,3,CThree boys convicted of their roles in
OL,4,Cthe rape of two girls in New Forest
OL,5,Ctown
OL,7,FJudge Nicholas Rowland adjourned the
OL,8,Fcase until a date to be set for
OL,9,Fsentencing reports to be prepared on
OL,10,Fthe three defendants, and released
OL,11,Fthem on conditional bail.
OL,13,FLucy Paddick, of the Crown Prosecution
OL,14,FService, said: "This is a deeply
OL,15,Fconcerning case which involved a
OL,16,Fdisturbing level of encouragement
OL,17,Fbetween young boys, who acted together
OL,18,Fto rape two young girls in separate
OL,19,Fincidents.
OL,26,@vD@POU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}  G11/13
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
